  "texts": [
    "Thus, in a full frame that is both separative and functional, a minimal valuation π making □ i p true at x is such that π(p) = ↓f i (x), or π(p) = ∅ if f i (x) is undefined.",
    "For simplicity, let us consider frames in which each f i is a total function, which validate the D axiom □ i p → ♢ i p. Note that in functional frames the♢ i clause (recall § 2.4) is that M, x ⊩ ♢ i φ iff ∀x ′ ⊑ x ∃y ⊑ f i (x ′): M, y ⊩ φ.Also note that if we have a functional frame F and obtain the modally equivalent standard frame F ↓ as in Lemma 6.17, then xR i↓ y iff y ⊑ f i (x).",
    "This equivalence is helpful when comparing the first-order correspondents in Examples 6.26 and 6.27.",
    "Example 6.27 (Functional Correspondence).",
    "Over separative full possibility frames in which each accessibility relation is a total function f i, we have the following global correspondences:• ♢ i p → □ i p corresponds to ∀x∀y ⊑ f i (x) ∃x ′ ⊑ x ∀z ⊑ f i (x ′) y ≬ z."
